<br>
By posting here, your effectively asking the server nicely to please don't mess with our planned raid.  In general I think this is a good idea, and will be fairly effective.  Guilds that could normally do Kael may pick another zone to hunt in on Tuesdays, if they know Tribulation will be there in the Arena, or at least that they want to be.  In line with that idea, that you want to inform people of your intent, its a good idea to be as informative as possible as to when you wanted to do Kael.  A generic reservation for all Tuesdays in the future is likely to be ignored.  <br>
<br>
It should be noted that guilds able to do Vindi or the Statue of Rallos Zek will likely not honor your wishes to have the Arena to yourselves in any case.  Both Vindi and the Statue are high demand mobs, and there is a competitiveness between guilds to do available spawns as and when they are available.  So its not unreasonable to expect FnF, Reso, or the restructuring AS to breeze past you in a swath of death as they move to engage the named mobs.  Though, they are likely to do so in such a manner as to make such an action as painless as possible.  <br>
<br>
If your going to camp popular locations (and Kael is), during prime time hours (which you prob will), you might have to expect to share the Arena for the 30 or 45 minutes it takes to buff, pull, and kill Vindi and/or Statue.  Of course if these mobs aren't present, you can expect no intrusion.<br>
<br>
There is also the issue of sharing Tuesdays.  I know at least two Kael Arena doable guilds that would look at Tuesdays as the only day they would also raid Kael Arena.  So they may take exception to your monopolization of the Kael Arena during prime time hours week after week, but until one of those two guilds take up the issue with you I'd try to inform the community of your intent on Tueadays as much as possible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udihce.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dihce</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><b>Perfection at it's Greatest </span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/5/02 10:11:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=139.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: There is no &quot;reserve&quot; system on FV </span><hr size=1> only on FV would someone pick apart a simple post.../shrug<br>
